<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1436,223,466]" pageId="7" pageNumber="585">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,368,367,393]" pageId="7" pageNumber="585">Identification.</emphasis>
This species was identified using the descriptions and illustrations by 
<bibRefCitation author="Schmid, F." box="[1212,1384,367,393]" pageId="7" pageNumber="585" pagination="1 - 126" refId="ref6761" refString="Schmid, F. (1982) La famille des Xiphocentronides (Trichoptera: Annulipalpia). Memoires de la Societe Entomologique du Canada, 121, 1 - 126. https: // doi. org / 10.4039 / entm 114122 fv" type="journal article" year="1982">Schmid (1982)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Vilarino, A. &amp; Santos Dias, E. &amp; Bispo, P. C." box="[151,388,403,430]" pageId="7" pageNumber="585" refId="ref7127" refString="Vilarino, A., Santos Dias, E. &amp; Bispo, P. C. (2021) Phylogeny indicates polyphyly in Cnodocentron (Trichoptera: Xiphocentronidae): biogeography and revision of New World species (Caenocentron). Zoological Journal of the Linnean Society, zlab 077. https: // doi. org / 10.1093 / zoolinnean / zlab 077" type="book" year="2021">
Vilarino 
<emphasis box="[249,297,403,429]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="585">et al</emphasis>
. (2021)
</bibRefCitation>
. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Schmid" authorityYear="1982" box="[398,634,403,430]" class="Insecta" family="Xiphocentronidae" genus="Caenocentron" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="585" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lausus">
<emphasis box="[398,634,403,430]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="585">Caenocentron lausus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is most similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Schmid 1982" authorityName="Schmid" authorityYear="1982" box="[837,1107,403,430]" class="Insecta" family="Xiphocentronidae" genus="Caenocentron" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="585" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="galesus">
<emphasis box="[837,953,403,430]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="585">C. galesus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Schmid, F." box="[959,1107,403,429]" pageId="7" pageNumber="585" pagination="1 - 126" refId="ref6761" refString="Schmid, F. (1982) La famille des Xiphocentronides (Trichoptera: Annulipalpia). Memoires de la Societe Entomologique du Canada, 121, 1 - 126. https: // doi. org / 10.4039 / entm 114122 fv" type="journal article" year="1982">Schmid 1982</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
but differs in the shape of the inferior appendage and in the lower piliferous area composed of setae of very different lengths.
</paragraph>
